cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a dictionary learning algorithm for denoising natural images, which involves machine learning and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The algorithm also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the efficacy of the algorithm in terms of peak signal-to-noise ratio (PSNR) and structural similarity index (SSIM), which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
